RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIXIE STREET was void of early speed then made a four wide bid at the three sixteenths pole, moved out to five or six wide in upper stretch and closed willingly and drove clear. HOSTILE AFLEET dueled in the second flight from the four path then made a bid on the turn to make a late run to prove second best. BASEBALL LOVER was rushed up to vie for the lead around the turn then took the lead at the eighth pole, drew clear but was caught in the final yards. BORN AGAIN GEORGE dueled in the second flight from the sixth path to the three eights pole, move out to four wide in upper stretch and closed well. MORRICONE dueled in the second flight from the inside to the five sixteenths and was out finished. MUCHO MARVIN dueled in the second flight from the five path to the seven sixteenths, made a three wide bid on the turn to improve position. BIBLEMAN went to a pressured lead to the eighth pole and tired. AZTAR dueled in the second flight from the two path to the seven sixteenths pole and finished evenly. G DON'T KNOW dueled in the second flight from the three path to the seven sixteenths pole but was not a threat. FAREWELL TIME was hustled along to press the pace from the inside and gave way.
